definition:
κλῆρος, -ου, ὁ 
 [in LXX chiefly for נַחֲלָה גּוֹרָל ;] 
a lot; 
   (a) that which is cast or drawn: Mat.27:35, Mrk.15:24, Luk.23:34, Jhn.19:24" (LXX), Act.1:26; 
   (b) that which is obtained by casting: Act.1:17 8:21; of a part in the Kingdom of God (cf. Wis 55), Act.26:18, Col.1:12; pl. of the "cure" of a presbyter, 1Pe.5:3 (see ICC, in l).†
 (AS)
